sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Direct MCP stdio client
    participant Server as VsMcpBridge.McpServer stdio
    participant Tool as bridge_get_tool_inventory
    participant Inventory as IBridgeToolInventoryService
    participant Catalog as IBridgeToolCatalog
    participant Snapshot as BridgeToolCatalogSnapshot
    participant Response as MCP tool response

    Client->>Server: initialize
    Server-->>Client: VsMcpBridge.McpServer 1.0.0.0
    Client->>Server: tools/list
    Server-->>Client: 17 tools including bridge_get_tool_inventory
    Client->>Server: tools/call bridge_get_tool_inventory
    Server->>Tool: invoke diagnostic method
    Tool->>Inventory: GetSnapshot()
    Inventory->>Catalog: GetTools()
    Catalog-->>Inventory: compiled descriptors
    Inventory->>Snapshot: map manifest metadata sorted by tool id
    Snapshot-->>Tool: bridge.bm25TextSearch, bridge.regexTextSearch
    Tool-->>Response: metadata-only JSON
    Response-->>Client: toolCount=2, callIsError=false

    Note over Tool,Catalog: No bridge tool ExecuteAsync call occurs during inventory.
    Note over Tool,Server: No approval, audit, pipe, ChatEngine, or payload/secret path was triggered by this diagnostic.
